          <title>Asteroid Samples Reveal Ancient Water World and Life-Giving Building Blocks</title>
          <description><![CDATA[NASA's Osiris-Rex spacecraft returns 122 grams of dust and pebbles from the near-Earth asteroid Bennu, delivering a sample canister to the Utah desert. Scientists analyze the samples and find evidence of sodium-rich minerals, amino acids, nitrogen in the form of ammonia, and parts of the genetic code.]]></description>
